The Aurora Highlands is the newest master-planned community in the Denver area and will eventually be home to 50,000 people. While the community offers homes at a variety of price points from a handful of builders, Bridgewater’s selection offers some of the community’s luxury options.
 
This new 4,000-acre master-planned community, with 21 miles of trails & 500 acres of parks and open space, is perfectly situated to connect you to major employment centers, the busy life of the city and a community of diverse and welcoming neighbors, recreation, schools, restaurants, shops and more.
 
Aurora Public Schools will eventually have four schools within The Aurora Highlands, the first of which opened up this school year.
 
Bridgewater Homes is a proud, local, female-lead company that started in Northern Colorado. Owner Leslie Bell is thrilled to expand Bridgewater Homes to The Aurora Highlands, which is the builder’s first time offering their homes in the Denver metro area.
 
Prices range from the mid-$600s to $1 million plus with seventeen different floor plan options to choose from. Some luxury amenities include a massive primary closet and bathroom, a movie theater, a gym and a basement bar. Bridgewater Homes offers highly customizable, bespoke options. That means residents have hundreds of cabinets, fixtures and finishes to choose from, which is a unique advantage of working with Bridgewater.

Bringing some clarity to a topic I’ve been thinking about quite a bit lately! 💭

During my open house the other day I mentioned that right now was a great time to buy and the woman said “really?!” In a shocked tone of voice. The answer is YES and let me tell you why. 

	1.	For every 1% that interest rates drop, 5 million buyers come back into the market, according to BlackRock. Don’t compete in the spring - you WILL be paying over list price. 💰
	2.	Given Denver’s seasonality🍁, the number of new listings to market will start to climb through the end of the year while the number of pending transactions stays stagnant, and even declines. This gap in the curve creates ~opportunity~. While everyone else is sitting on the sidelines, your finding deals and getting reductions on purchase price, or better yet, getting seller concessions that help you to get to a rate in the 5’s or 6’s. 
	3.	The cost of waiting is just too high! On avg, the Denver Metro has appreciated by 8% on average since 2010. Meaning, you’re missing out on that appreciation by waiting on another year. If you’re purchasing a million dollar home that is $80,000! ($40K on a $500K home). I can speak to this personally. We bought our home almost 4 years ago (in Fall so we got a great deal) and have seen over 50% appreciation in our home’s value 😱🤯📈 

Questions on this? Let’s chat 💬

1. Truth! September through the end of the year is the when you will find the best deals. Inventory sitting for longer means more motivated sellers negotiating power. When spring comes, you can throw that out the window and expect to compete with multiple buyers, paying 100%+ of the listing price. I just helped my buyers negotiate an $18,000 discount on the purchase, plus a brand new $16,000 roof. 🏠 

2. Truth! I just helped some first time home buyers purchase a home with $0 down and actually got a credit at closing. Message me if you’re curious how 👀 For non first time home buyers, you can buy a home with as little as 3% down, depending on your qualifications and the property.

3. Lie! While securing a low-interest rate is crucial, it’s not the sole factor to consider. The overall cost of the loan, including fees, closing costs, and the loan term, should also be evaluated. Consult your real estate agent for advice on the best long-term options for you.

3 tips for brides to keep your wedding day stress free… 🤍

1. Make sure you have EVERYTHING done the night before any of the festivities start, and be thorough with it… this includes, writing your vows, steaming any clothing, setting your jewlrey out, giving your bridesmaids their outfits or special bags. The last thing you want is to feel frantic the morning of trying to cross last minute things off your to do list. 

2. Go to bed early the night before and have a slow morning by yourself. I woke up at 8 and went outside for some fresh air & sunshine.  I had some fresh fruit & coffee while I re-read my vows and meditated… I can’t tell you how this set me up to feel so present the rest of the day. It felt like everything was in slow motion. 🥺

3. Have your designated space to get ready separate from your bridesmaids (especially if you have 13 like I did 🤪). As much as I love them, we all know it’s absolute chaos trying to get that many girls ready at once. Have someone there to make sure everyone is getting hair & makeup done on time and to run point on photos. 

.

Little reminders ✨ Happy News Years, Friends. Looking forward to 2024 ❤️

I was nervous to post this… 

I was hesitant because I didn’t want people to receive this as boasting or think “that’s nothing… so and so sold this many millions”, but 2024 is going to be a year of fearlessness, authenticy, and truly not giving a damn what other people think. 

2023 rounded out my first 12 months of being a licensed real estate agent and I’m giving myself permission to be proud of what I accomplished. It was hands down the hardest year I’ve experienced both mentally and physically. This job comes with so many challenges that I never could’ve expected and truly tested my strength. I want nothing more than to overcome my self doubts and continue serving clients in such an important way. 

From the bottom of my heart, thank you so much to my clients who trusted me, friends and family who supported me, and my incredible mentor @deviree . I couldn’t have done it without you, and am excited to see what 2024 brings 🫶🏼💃🏽🪩

This one’s for all the busy girls 🤪 hair is my least favorite part of getting ready but this is how I slap it together in less than 10 minutes. Lately I prefer my Revlon blowout brush over my Dyson since my hair so long!

The @colorwowhair products are my absolute fave! I have fine hair so most other products weigh my hair down too much but these are perfect and give some much volume. 

1. Wash hair & use @colorwowhair #moneymask 
2. Towel dry hair, brush, and spray dream coat on ends with Raise the Root. Brush it out. 
3. Rough dry with blow dryer 
4. Section hair off and start blowing out with Dyson or revlon blow dry brush 
5. Use volumizing mouse on top sections of hair
